<paragraph id="1B2F252ACE2802136DD0F8A66268315E" blockId="18.[132,680,1816,1872]" lastBlockId="18.[718,1267,184,656]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE2802136DD0F8A666C8373E" box="[132,232,1817,1840]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Discussão:</emphasis>
A presença das costas elirais sub-umerais coloca 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE2802136D9BF8876711375E" authority="Curletti &amp; Migliore, 2014" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Migliore" authorityYear="2014" box="[207,305,1848,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE2802136D9BF8876711375E" box="[207,305,1848,1872]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">A. vanini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="32D74443CE2802136C6FF88767AE3741" box="[315,398,1848,1871]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
em um grupo de espécies bem caracterizadas, que no 
<collectingCountry id="638765BACE2802136974FF07627930DE" box="[1056,1113,184,208]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Brasil</collectingCountry>
compreende: 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE2802136F9AFF6765C330FE" authority="Obenberger 1933" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1933" box="[718,995,216,240]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Paradomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mrazi">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE2802136F9AFF67650530FE" box="[718,805,216,240]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">A. mrazi</emphasis>
Obenberger 1933
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE2802136EB9FF676566311E" authority="Gory &amp; Laporte 1837" authorityName="Gory &amp; Laporte" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictipennis">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE2802136EB9FF67625330FE" box="[1005,1139,216,240]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">A. pictipennis</emphasis>
Gory &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="7F0158DBCE2802136984FF676566311E" author="LAPORTE &amp; DE CASTELNAU &amp; F. L. N. CAUMONT DE &amp; H. L. GORY" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" pagination="12 - 16" refId="ref15428" refString="LAPORTE [DE CASTELNAU], F. L. N. CAUMONT DE &amp; H. L. GORY. 1837. Histoire naturelle de iconographie des insectes Coleopteres. Monographie des buprestides. P. Dumenil, Paris. Volume 1, livraisons 12 - 16, genera: Buprestis (pp. 65 - 160), Nascio, Acherusia, Asthraeus, Bulis, Acantha, Apatura (genera paged separately). [see Gory &amp; Laporte for Volume 2 and Gory for Volume 4]." type="journal article" year="1837">Laporte 1837</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE2802136E00FF4762A6311E" authority="Obenberger 1933" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1933" box="[852,1158,248,272]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vinitius">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE2802136E00FF47659F311E" box="[852,959,248,272]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">A. vinitius</emphasis>
Obenberger 1933
</taxonomicName>
. De todas essas espécies diferencia-se pelas menores dimensões, pela coloração e pelos élitros glabros.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2F252ACE2802136E53FEE7628B329E" blockId="18.[718,1267,184,656]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
Esse grupo poderia apresentar um dimorfismo sexual acetuado: o síntipo de 
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE2802136EAEFEC76278319E" box="[1018,1112,376,400]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE2802136EAEFEC76274319E" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1933" box="[1018,1108,376,400]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Paradomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mrazi">A. mrazi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
conservado no NHML é um macho e, ao contrário dos cinco síntipos fêmeas, presentes no NMPC, é caracterizado pelo pronoto azul e os élitros roxos; possui coloração semelhante a 
<taxonomicName id="DC905EA9CE2802136FADFE476576321E" authority="Curletti &amp; Migliore, 2014" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Migliore" authorityYear="2014" box="[761,854,504,528]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="29E4F938CE2802136FADFE476576321E" box="[761,854,504,528]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">A. vanini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="32D74443CE2802136E09FE47658B3201" box="[861,939,504,527]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
com margem do pronoto e calo umeral verdes. Todavia, o macho da espécie de Obenberger diferencia-se pela pubescência em formato Y na metade basal dos élitros, pela carena pré-umeral inteira e pelos urosternitos uniformenete pubescentes.
</paragraph>
